comment:
* Information about the status of the location-based time zone detection algorithm.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: PROVIDER_STATUS_NOT_PRESENT
variables.comment:
* Indicates a provider is not present because it has not been configured, the configuration
     * is bad, or the provider has reported a permanent failure.

variables.name: PROVIDER_STATUS_NOT_READY
variables.comment:
* Indicates a provider has not reported it is certain or uncertain. This may be because it has
     * just started running, or it has been stopped.

variables.name: PROVIDER_STATUS_IS_CERTAIN
variables.comment: * Indicates a provider last reported it is certain.

variables.name: PROVIDER_STATUS_IS_UNCERTAIN
variables.comment: * Indicates a provider last reported it is uncertain.

variables.name: NOT_SUPPORTED
variables.comment: * An instance used when the location algorithm is not supported by the device.

variables.name: RUNNING_NOT_REPORTED
variables.comment: * An instance used when the location algorithm is running, but has not reported an event.

variables.name: NOT_RUNNING
variables.comment: * An instance used when the location algorithm is supported but not running.

methods.name: public int getStatus()
methods.comment: * Returns the status value of the detection algorithm.

methods.name: public int getPrimaryProviderStatus()
methods.comment:
* Returns the status of the primary location time zone provider as categorized by the detection
     * algorithm.

methods.name: public TimeZoneProviderStatus getPrimaryProviderReportedStatus()
methods.comment:
* Returns the status of the primary location time zone provider as reported by the provider
     * itself. Can be {@code null} when the provider hasn't reported, or omitted when it has.

methods.name: public int getSecondaryProviderStatus()
methods.comment:
* Returns the status of the secondary location time zone provider as categorized by the
     * detection algorithm.

methods.name: public TimeZoneProviderStatus getSecondaryProviderReportedStatus()
methods.comment:
* Returns the status of the secondary location time zone provider as reported by the provider
     * itself. Can be {@code null} when the provider hasn't reported, or omitted when it has.

methods.name: public static LocationTimeZoneAlgorithmStatus parseCommandlineArg(@NonNull String arg)
methods.comment:
* Parses a {@link LocationTimeZoneAlgorithmStatus} from a toString() string for manual
     * command-line testing.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel parcel, int flags)
public boolean couldEnableTelephonyFallback()
methods.comment:
* Returns {@code true} if the algorithm status could allow the time zone detector to enter
     * telephony fallback mode.

methods.name: public static String providerStatusToString(@ProviderStatus int providerStatus)
public static int providerStatusFromString(@Nullable String providerStatusString)
private static boolean hasProviderReported(@ProviderStatus int providerStatus)
